         <abstract>
            <p>We extend a result of Ramare and Rumely, 1996, about the Chebyshev function θ in arithmetic progressions. We find a map ε(x) such that <tex-math>$| \theta(x; k, l) - x/\varphi (k) | &lt; x\varepsilon (x)$</tex-math> and <tex-math>$\varepsilon (x) = O (\frac{1}{ln^a x}) (\forall a &gt; 0)$</tex-math>, whereas ε(x) is a constant. Now we are able to show that, for x ⩾ 1531, <tex-math>$| \theta (x; 3, l) - x/2 | &lt; 0.262 \frac {x}{ln x}$</tex-math> and, for x ⩾ 151, <tex-math>$\pi(x; 3, l) &gt; \frac{x}{2 ln x}.$</tex-math>
            </p>
          </abstract>
